<section class="hero container">
  <div class="hero-text">
    <p class="eyebrow">Cognitive Neuroscientist · Freie Universität Berlin</p>
    <h1>Neural dynamics of conscious perception across brain rhythms, behavior, and neuroimaging.</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      I study perception, consciousness, neural entrainment, and brain oscillations using M/EEG, fMRI, tACS, and computational modelling.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="hero-image">
    <img src="photo_YCC.jpg" alt="Portrait of Yuranny Cabral-Calderin">
  </div>
</section>
  
<section id="about" class="section section-light">
  <div class="container">
  <h2>About</h2>
  <p>
    Cognitive Neuroscientist at Freie Universität Berlin working on perception,
    consciousness, and neural oscillations across sensory and cognitive domains.
  </p>
  <p>
    My research combines psychophysics, EEG/MEG, intracranial recordings, fMRI,
    and non-invasive brain stimulation to understand how brain rhythms shape conscious experience.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="research" class="section section-white">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Research</h2>
  <div class="cards">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Conscious perception</h3>
      <p>Neural mechanisms of conscious perception across modalities.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Neural entrainment</h3>
      <p>How rhythmic input and stimulation influence behavior.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Multimodal imaging</h3>
      <p>Combining EEG, MEG, fMRI and brain stimulation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

